cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new framework for synthesizing handwritten stroke data using a generative adversarial network. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper deals with image processing and specifically focuses on generating handwritten text. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new model for generating sequential handwritten data using a recurrent latent variable model. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with generating text, specifically handwritten text. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a new discriminator consisting of an integrated CNN-LSTM based feature extraction with Path Signature Features (PSF) as input and a Feedforward Neural Network (FNN) based binary classifier.
